---

<ServiceLayout
  title="MOFA Attestation Dubai | Ministry of Foreign Affairs Document Legalization"
  description="MOFA attestation services in Dubai. Ministry of Foreign Affairs document legalization for educational, personal, and commercial documents. Complete attestation chain coordination."
  keywords="mofa attestation dubai, ministry of foreign affairs attestation, document legalization uae, mofa authentication, uae document attestation"
  heroTitle="MOFA Attestation"
  heroSubtitle="Ministry of Foreign Affairs"
  heroIntro="MOFA attestation is the final step in legalizing foreign documents for UAE use. The Ministry of Foreign Affairs verifies that your documents have properly completed the international authentication chain, making them officially valid for government submissions, court proceedings, and business transactions."
  snapshot={snapshot}
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  faqs={faqs}
  serviceType="MOFA Attestation Service"
  processSteps={processSteps}
  processTitle="Our MOFA Attestation Process"
  accordionSections={accordionSections}
>
  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Understanding MOFA's Role</h2>
      <p>The Ministry of Foreign Affairs serves as the UAE government's final verification point for foreign documents. When you present an attested document to a UAE court, employer, or government agency, they trust it because MOFA has confirmed the authenticity of the entire authentication chain.</p>
      
      <p>MOFA doesn't verify the document content itselfâ€”they verify that proper authentication procedures were followed. Their stamp confirms that a legitimate UAE Embassy attested the document, which in turn confirmed Foreign Ministry authentication from the issuing country.</p>
      
      <p>This chain of trust is why attempting to skip steps doesn't work. A document with only embassy attestation (no prior foreign ministry authentication) will be rejected by MOFA. A document with foreign ministry authentication but no embassy attestation cannot proceed. Each step verifies the previous one.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Related Services</h2>
      <div class="related-grid">
        <a href="/services/attestation/" class="related-card">
          <h3>Attestation Guide</h3>
          <p>Complete attestation services overview</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/services/attestation/embassy/" class="related-card">
          <h3>Embassy Legalization</h3>
          <p>UAE Embassy attestation coordination</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/services/attestation/india/" class="related-card">
          <h3>India Attestation</h3>
          <p>Complete chain for Indian documents</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</ServiceLayout>

<style>
  .related-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .related-card {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--bg-light, #f8f9fa);
    border-radius: 8px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--primary-color);
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  
  .related-card:hover {
    border-left-color: var(--accent-color);
    background: white;
  }
  
  .related-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    color: var(--primary-color);
  }
  
  .related-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
